<HEADLINE>
<P>
THE MANY VIEWS OF 'DAYS OF RAGE' 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
On every other issue of concern to Americans, no matter how controversial, both 
sides have been publicly presented: pro-life vs. pro-choice; hawks vs. doves 
over Vietnam; pro-glasnost vs. anti-communists, to name but a few. Why must the 
Palestinian-Israeli conflict be the exception? Those who have protested against 
"Days of Rage" on the ground of bias should consider that sometimes the facts 
are biased. 
</P>
<P>
MOHAMMED BARAKAT 
</P>
<P>
Los Angeles 
</P>
</TEXT>
