</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
South Africa's tennis union has been suspended by the International Tennis 
Federation because of the country's policy of apartheid. 
</P>
<P>
The move prevents tennis from losing its recently gained Olympic status, said 
ITF president Phillippe Chartrier of France at an annual meeting in Buenos 
Aires. 
</P>
