</P>
</LENGTH>
<HEADLINE>
<P>
PULSAR DATA SYSTEMS NAMED AN IBM DEALER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From United Press International 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
LANDOVER, Md. 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Pulsar Data Systems has been selected as the first minority company to become 
an IBM advanced product dealer, the company has announced. 
</P>
<P>
Under the agreement, IBM will provide Pulsar with the complete advanced product 
line networking products. 
</P>
<P>
Pulsar, a 7-year-old systems integration firm based in Landover with major 
facilities in Newark, Del., will focus its marketing efforts on federal, state 
and municipal government agencies as well as the prime contractor community. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Wire 
</P>
</TYPE>
<SUBJECT>
<P>
MINORITY OWNED BUSINESS; INTERNATIONAL BUSINESS MACHINES CORP; COMPUTERS; 
COMPUTER INDUSTRY; PULSAR DATA SYSTEMS 
</P>
</SUBJECT>
