<HEADLINE>
<P>
ROUNDUP; 
</P>
<P>
RIDDLE RUNS RANCHO ALAMITOS TO 9-7 VICTORY OVER COSTA MESA 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Dana Riddle rushed for 317 yards in 37 carries to lead Rancho Alamitos High 
School to a 9-7 victory over Costa Mesa in a nonleague football game Friday at 
Garden Grove High School. 
</P>
<P>
Riddle scored Rancho Alamitos' only touchdown on a 95-yard run in the first 
quarter. Playing inside linebacker, he also gave Rancho Alamitos two points 
with a fourth-quarter safety. 
</P>
<P>
"He had a 48-yard run called back because of holding in the third quarter," 
Rancho Alamitos Coach Mark Miller said. "It's too bad we had so much called 
back or he could have had 400 yards." 
</P>
<P>
Costa Mesa scored on a 56-yard pass from Duby Ostina to David Phillips in the 
second quarter. 
</P>
<P>
In other nonleague games: 
</P>
<P>
Fullerton 21, Whittier 0 -- The Indians (2-0) scored two first-quarter 
touchdowns and used a strong defensive effort in front of 2,100 at Cal High. 
</P>
<P>
Early in the first quarter, Fullerton fullback Marcus Roberson ran 75 yards 
with a short pass from Rene Arias for the first touchdown. Later in the first 
quarter, tailback Chris Escalera ran five yards on an option play for the 
second touchdown. 
</P>
<P>
Arias completed a three-yard pass to Bobby Patel for the final score midway 
through the second quarter. 
</P>
<P>
The defense "did a superb job stopping the run all night long," Fullerton Coach 
Reginald Hill said. 
</P>
<P>
Troy 46, El Dorado 0 -- Chad Brasington scored three touchdowns to lead the 
Warriors (2-0) in front of 2,000 at Fullerton High School. Brasington scored on 
runs of 35, 11 and four yards and finished with 75 yards rushing. Quarterback 
Greg Windle threw a pair of touchdown passes, both to wide receiver Ryan 
Russell. Windle connected with Russell on a 30-yard touchdown pass in the first 
quarter. The two teamed again on a 17-yard scoring play in the second quarter. 
Eldon Davis also scored two touchdowns on runs of one and four yards. Troy 
forced seven turnovers in posting its second consecutive shutout. El Dorado is 
0-2. 
</P>
<P>
Esperanza 20, Barstow 6 -- Senior tailback Lance Brown ran for two touchdowns 
at Valencia High School. Brown finished with 128 yards in 12 carries. 
</P>
<P>
Mayfair 26, Garden Grove 9 -- Quarterback David Partin completed five of 15 
passes for 69 yards and two touchdowns and fullback Marvin Morton rushed for 
102 yards in 18 carries as Mayfair won its second consecutive game. Garden 
Grove is 1-1. 
</P>
<P>
Walnut 20, Magnolia 9 -- Linebacker Dave Flores, a 5-foot-5, 150-pound junior, 
led a stingy Mustang defense with a 85-yard interception return for a 
first-quarter touchdown to pace the visitors in a nonleague game at Western 
High School. Flores also had a fumble recovery as the Mustangs held Magnolia to 
minus 35 yards rushing. 
</P>
<P>
For the Sentinels (0-2), senior running back caught four passes for 97 yards 
and Magnolia's lone touchdown. Magnolia quarterback Elliott Parker was nine of 
16 for 168 yards, but had two interceptions, including the one by Flores. 
</P>
<P>
On offense, visiting Walnut (1-1) featured a balanced rushing attack which ran 
up 183 yards and saw four players gain more than 40 yards apiece. Corona del 
Mar 9, Marina 0 -- Fullback Jerrott Willard caught a 10-yard touchdown pass 
from quarterback Todd Kehrli and kicked a 44-yard field goal to account for all 
of Corona del Mar's scoring at Davidson Field. 
</P>
<P>
In eight-man nonleague football: 
</P>
<P>
Claremont-Garden Grove 34, Ambassador Baptist 8 -- Eric Tessaorre scored three 
touchdowns and had nine rushes for 82 yards to lead visiting Claremont. 
Claremont was in control the whole way and had a 26-0 lead at halftime. 
</P>
