<HEADLINE>
<P>
MADISON RALLY TOO MUCH FOR SAN CLEMENTE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The San Clemente High School football team outplayed visiting San Diego Madison 
for three quarters, but was itself outplayed in the fourth and ended up on the 
short end of a 20-10 score in front of about 1,000 Friday night. 
</P>
<P>
The Tritons (0-2) were in front, 10-6, at the half, but after a scoreless third 
quarter, they gave up two touchdowns to the Warhawks (1-1). 
</P>
<P>
On the first play of the quarter, quarterback Mike Jones passed 32 yards to 
James Cole for a 13-10 lead. The play completed a 61-yard, five-play drive. 
</P>
<P>
