Bryant Craig with 1:21 remaining. 
</P>
<P>
Madison scored first on Cole's 60-yard interception return of a Mario Watkins 
pass midway through the first quarter. The conversion try failed and Madison 
led, 6-0. 
</P>
<P>
Then it was all San Clemente until halftime. Triton fullback Larry Brophy tied 
the game on the next play from scrimmage, scoring on an 80-yard run up the 
middle. A successful conversion gave San Clemente a 7-6 lead. Derek Marshall's 
39-yard field goal gave the Tritons a 10-7 lead at the intermission. 
