<HEADLINE>
<P>
SCC NAMES PHILLIPS ITS BASEBALL COACH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Charlie Phillips has been named baseball coach at Southern California College, 
the school said Friday. 
</P>
<P>
Phillips, 33, replaces Doug Adams, who resigned in August to become an 
assistant coach at UC Irvine. Phillips was an assistant at Saddleback College 
last season and was the pitching coach at Orange Coast from 1987 to '88. 
</P>
<P>
He was an all-Southern Section selection at La Quinta High School and played on 
USC's 1974 national championship team. 
</P>
<P>
SCC was 30-21 and finished second in the Golden State Athletic Conference last 
season under Adams. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<SUBJECT>
<P>
COACHES; COLLEGE ATHLETICS; SOUTHERN CALIFORNIA COLLEGE; BASEBALL 
</P>
