<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY COLLEGE ROUNDUP; 
</P>
<P>
GOLDEN WEST REACHES WATER POLO SEMIFINAL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Golden West College won two matches Friday at the Cuesta water polo tournament 
to advance to the semifinal round. 
</P>
<P>
The Rustlers defeated San Diego Mesa, 17-5, in the quarterfinals after beating 
College of the Sequoias, 17-6, earlier on Friday. 
</P>
<P>
Henry Rebello had four goals and Greg LaPointe three for Golden West in the 
Mesa game. 
</P>
<P>
Steve Kidder and Rebello had four goals and Matt Mauser had three in the 
victory over Sequoias. Golden West plays two-time defending state champion Long 
Beach today at 10:30 a.m. Long Beach has won 11 of the last 13 matches with 
Golden West. 
</P>
<P>
In other Cuesta tournament water polo matches: 
</P>
<P>
Cuesta 9, Saddleback 7 -- Tino Perong had three goals for Saddleback in the 
Gauchos'second-round loss. Saddleback had defeated Cerritos, 11-9, in the first 
round. Perong had five goals and Dave Becker three for Saddleback, which will 
play Orange Coast at 9:30 a.m. today in the consolation round. 
</P>
<P>
In nonconference women's volleyball: 
</P>
<P>
Cypress 3, MiraCosta 2 -- Cypress (2-0) was led by freshman Karen Lane who had 
21 kills, 17 assists and five aces in Cypress' 15-17, 15-12, 15-8, 8-15, 15-6, 
victory. Cypress' Kari Calliham had 11 kills, four blocks and three aces. 
MiraCosta is 0-1. 
</P>
<P>
Saddleback 3, Alan Hancock 0 -- Cyndi Rhone had 16 kills to help Saddleback to 
a 15-2, 15-11, 15-10 sweep at Alan Hancock. 
</P>
</TEXT>
