<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY SWAP MEETS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Clipboard researched by Kathie Bozanich and Susan Davis Greene / Los Angeles 
Times; Graphics by Thomas Penix / Los Angeles Times 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
It has been said that one man's trash can be another man's treasure. The myriad 
of swap meets in Orange County lends some credence to that viewpoint. 
</P>
<P>
Vendors, open-air stalls, an array of colorful gadgets, eager-beaver shoppers, 
junk dealers, new and "previously owned" wares give the swap meet attendees an 
almost old-fashioned carnival atmosphere. Haggling is expected and is part of 
the excitement. 
</P>
<P>
Here are the county "swaps" and the particulars: 
</P>
<P>
1. CYPRESS SWAP MEET 
</P>
<P>
9200 Valley View St. 
</P>
<P>
Cypress 
</P>
<P>
(714) 952-9355 
</P>
<P>
Hours: 6:30 a.m. to 4 p.m. Saturday and Sunday 
</P>
<P>
Admission and parking: free 
</P>
<P>
Vendor information: 380 spaces available; rates are $12 a day for a 
21-by-21-foot or 28-by-21-foot space; prime spaces available for $13-$30 a day; 
must pay in cash; space reservations up to two weeks in advance through the 
office at 5732 Camp St., Cypress, (714) 952-9847. Hours: 1 to 6 p.m. Tuesday 
and Wednesday, noon to 5 p.m. Thursday, and 9 a.m. to noon Friday. Requires 
city vending license. After three rentals, must purchase a retail license from 
State Board of Equalization with above address. A 10% discount for monthly 
space. 
</P>
<P>
Sales restrictions: Call for information 
</P>
<P>
2. GOLDEN WEST COLLEGE 
</P>
<P>
15744 Golden West St. 
</P>
<P>
Huntington Beach 
</P>
<P>
(714) 893-2389 
</P>
<P>
Hours: 8 a.m. to 3 p.m. Saturday and Sunday 
</P>
<P>
Admission and parking: free 
</P>
<P>
Vendor information: 600 spaces on Saturday, 350 on Sunday; rates are $12 in 
advance, $16 morning of meet. Advance space reservations taken in person on a 
cash-only basis from 1 to 4 p.m. Tuesdays, Thursdays and Fridays and from 9:30 
to 11:30 a.m. Saturdays and Sundays in Security Building; only monthly vendors 
may reserve by telephone or mail. 
</P>
<P>
Sales restrictions: Food and beverages 
</P>
<P>
Miscellaneous: Most merchandise is handicrafts and used goods 
</P>
<P>
3. INDOOR SWAP MEET OF STANTON 
</P>
