10401 Beach Blvd. 
</P>
<P>
Stanton 
</P>
<P>
(714) 527-1234 
</P>
<P>
Hours: noon to 8 p.m. Friday, 10 a.m. to 6 p.m. Saturday and Sunday 
</P>
<P>
Admission: free on Fridays and $1 on Saturday and Sunday; always free for 
children under 12 accompanied by adults and senior citizens over 60; parking is 
free 
</P>
<P>
Vendor information: spaces are $300-$450, 8 feet by 12 feet. Must have resale 
license and license from city of Stanton. Credit check is mandatory 
</P>
<P>
Sales restrictions: Except for antiques, merchandise sold must be new and not 
duplicate that being sold by other vendors 
</P>
<P>
Miscellaneous: Aisles, bathrooms and elevators accommodate handicapped 
</P>
<P>
4. ORANGE COAST COLLEGE 
</P>
<P>
2701 Fairview Road 
</P>
<P>
Costa Mesa 
</P>
<P>
(714) 432-0202 
</P>
<P>
Hours: 8 a.m. to 3 p.m. Saturday and Sunday 
</P>
<P>
Admission and parking: free 
</P>
<P>
Vendor information: $12 in advance for 8-foot by 20-foot space (includes room 
for vehicle); Must buy space in advance from 9 a.m. to 1 p.m. Wednesday, 
Thursday or Friday at the Community Services Building, cash only. Retail 
license from the State Board of Equalization required 
</P>
<P>
Sales restrictions: No food 
</P>
<P>
5. ORANGE COUNTY MARKETPLACE 
</P>
<P>
88 Fair Drive, 
</P>
<P>
Costa Mesa 
</P>
<P>
(714) 640-4633 
</P>
<P>
Hours: 7 a.m. to 4 p.m. Saturday and Sunday 
</P>
<P>
Admission: 50 cents; children under 12 free; parking is free 
</P>
<P>
Vendor information: $25-$100 per space per day, 15 feet by 27 feet. New 
merchandise preferred. Retail license from State Board of Equalization with 
above address required 
</P>
<P>
Sales restrictions: No live animals 
</P>
<P>
6. PACIFIC ANAHEIM SWAP MEET 
</P>
